##Wuhan Epidemic Prevention: How to make good use of the existing resources?

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

As of January 28, the National Health Commission said it had sent nearly 6,000 medical teams to Hubei to support the prevention and control of the disease. Across the country medical personnel and material relief, is slowly changing the Wuhan response to the status quo. Wuhan is also constantly summing up and adjusting its response measures. With the increasing number of imported cases, the operational experience and lessons in epidemic prevention in Wuhan may be used for reference by other regions.
According to Miao Xiaohui, a clinical consultant on public health in Shanghai, it is important to expand the site of a new hospital in Wuhan, but how to deploy existing resources and respond quickly is even more important.
By Wang Haiyan

By Wang Haiyan

The problem at all levels of the hospital

▲▲▲

The problem at all levels of the hospital

▲▲▲

At noon on January 24, the Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Prevention and control headquarters announced that patients with fever will be sent from the community to the Community Medical Center, screened and classified, and then transported to higher hospitals. But for some patients, the problem has gotten worse.

Xu Cai, whose father-in-law, mother-in-law and husband became feverish on January 10 and 15, respectively, and has been receiving injections in the hospital and taking CT scans, all showing double lung infections, and rule out a stream, B stream and other pneumonia, but can not confirm new coronary pneumonia. On January 23, the city of Wuhan was closed, public transportation stopped, Xu Caijia did not have a car, the patient began walking to and from the hospital. Already breathing heavily, Xu Cai's in laws walk for two hours on a two kilometer road.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the afternoon of January 25, Xu's husband had a fever. In accordance with the grading policy, Xu called his neighborhood committee, but the line was busy all day. No one answered at the Community Hospital. Until 10 pm, the community finally contact Xu Cai, suggested that she overcome it, but at this time Xu Cai husband has a long high fever, fever medicine is also useless.

Xu Cai can only go over the community, directly dial 120. At 3:00 am on the first day of the Lunar New Year, Xu Cai finally found an ambulance and picked up her husband after spending more than two hours on the phone with her friends. The first stop was Tianyou Hospital in Wuhan, a newly announced designated hospital, but after the ambulance arrived, the hospital was told that it was still clearing the beds and could not receive treatment. The ambulance had to take the person to the eleven hospital, which was the designated hospital where Xu Cai's husband had been receiving injections. The subsequent lung CT results showed that Xu Cai's husband's infection was getting worse.

But Eleven hospital can not arrange hospitalization, one is no beds, two is in accordance with the new classification policy, hospitalization must be reported from community channels, after diagnosis unified arrangements. Xu Cai and the friend many seek a relation, the reply of many hospitals is such. Xu Cai can only urge the community repeatedly, and the only feedback the community can give is that it has declared, do not know when the results.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Expedition photography

On the morning of January 26, two days after the grading plan was announced, our reporter randomly dialed 10 Street office landlines in various districts, half of which were not answered, and two street offices could help arrange vehicles and report them, two street offices said they were in charge of grading medical information, but could not guarantee vehicles and so on. Our reporter also called 10 community hospitals and neighborhood phone, a total of 3 units connected, 2 said a car, can run through the flow, 1 said they do not know the situation.

In fact, before the community diagnosis and treatment, there has been a set of grading diagnosis and treatment process, that is, the former general hospital admitted to the designated hospital fever patients to designated hospitals, designated hospitals confirmed serious patients to Golden Pool Hospital. It is equally difficult to get through every link here, a doctor from a top-three hospital told this newspaper, "after the announcement of the Sentinel System, the Sentinel Hospital in our district set a condition that it must be a confirmed patient. At the moment, the number of test kits is very small. According to this standard, the patients we have will not be able to get out at all for a while. But the doctors have already provided support, and we have also admitted patients from other departments in designated hospitals to our hospital. We can only do our best to maintain normal operation."

Hospitals have problems, too. Li Tong, a nurse at a designated hospital, told the magazine that the Respiratory Department of the hospital was full at the end of December, and in early January several floors of wards had been vacated for fever patients. On the night of January 21st, the hospital was told to become a designated hospital for new pneumonia, and more patients immediately flocked to the hospital, lining up outside the door for hundreds of meters, hard to digest.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As the current Terminal Jinyintan hospital, need to confirm and transfer procedures to be admitted, "access" strict, the number of relatively controllable, the problem here is a serious lack of medical staff. Charles Lindbergh was a nurse at Golden Pond, and she and her partners volunteered to work in nursing at Wuhan hospitals. There were nearly 40 patients on the first floor, only 8 nurses on the day shift and only 3 nurses on the night shift. They were responsible for everything from injections to eating, drinking, defecating, scattering and washing. Among them, in the critical ward, in addition to full body protective clothing, nurses were responsible for everything, also carry up to 10 pounds of ventilation circulatory system, each time up to only stay about 3 hours, or there is the risk of shock.

There is no place for medical staff to rest in Jinyintan hospital. The medical staff who are in close contact with critically ill patients every day can only go home after work and can not be completely isolated. To build up resistance, Charles Lindbergh and colleagues took a daily dose of traditional Chinese Medicine and Thymosin, an immunomodulator with an uncertain protective effect. Because of the priority of protection materials for Jinyintan hospital, their protection materials are still sufficient.

Suddenly became a designated hospital

▲▲▲

Suddenly became a designated hospital

Hospitals at all levels are facing a huge shortage of materials, which is related to the dramatic increase in the number of patients consulted and the lack of preparation. On Jan. 22, Ms. Li recalled, their hospital became a designated hospital, a surprise announcement. Li's department does not specialize in breathing, but has previously treated several hospitalized patients with a high degree of suspected new coronavirus pneumonia. At that time in addition to ordinary masks, Li Tong in the department, all medical staff without any protective measures, is a "streaking" state. On January 17th, there were several suspected infected people among the medical staff, and the medical staff strongly requested protective equipment, but could not obtain the result. A few days later, around January 20, the nurses'cloth nurses'hats were finally replaced with disposable hats.

The News that oneself unit becomes fixed-point hospital, Li Tong and patient almost at the same time know. This means that a steady stream of feverish patients have flooded the gates, and hospitals are scrambling to install isolation doors and transform infectious disease wards. The hospital only had two days to buffer, two days, Li Tong to his patients discharge or transfer, only to receive a slot in the only training, learned to wear off protective clothing. Finally, the protective gear was not officially issued until the evening of January 23.

The rush to respond poses a risk to health care workers. On January 23, Li Tong's hospital had a blood test for all medical staff. In the department where Li Tong is located, several people were isolated at home, while dozens of medical staff throughout the hospital needed hospital treatment, the shortage of medical staff has become more serious. At the time of this reporter's interview, one of Li Tong's colleagues had been working for 18 hours straight.

Wu Hong, who runs a third Tier Hospital in Wuhan, said the government had made no arrangements for medical staff after the city was shut down. Wu's home is far from the hospital, and he usually travels by public transportation. On the first day of the city closure, he spent more than an hour just taking a taxi. Some of his colleagues who live a little closer can only cycle to work. The hospital initially even the protection material and the basic people's Livelihood Material Transportation Channel All did not have, until many hospitals appeal, only then opens a specialized transportation channel.

Like most hospitals, Wu Hong's hospital is short of masks, he said, referring to a hospital with 500 people, at a minimum, one a day for each person, and 5,000 masks for 10 days. "How can one mask per person per day, how can doctors use only one mask for many operations per day? " In order to reduce the use, the hospital can only try to divide the work schedule for medical staff, reducing the working hours of staff in non-key departments. This, in turn, exacerbates the strain on medical resources.

The shortage of protective products is related to the surge in usage and the shutdown of factories during the Spring Festival. Hospitals seldom stock up on protective products. But according to Wu Hong, there is a reserve at the municipal level, and the reason it has not been released is because the Wuhan version of the "Xiaotangshan Hospital" is under construction and needs to meet the needs of the new hospital. At present, the major hospitals are trying to find their own way to the community to raise funds for protective materials. "In raising money, the government should put out supplies first and then raise money from society, " Wu Hong said. "Now it's the other way around. "

On the evening of January 24, the third press conference on the prevention and control of the new coronary lung disease in Hubei Province was held. According to the Hubei Provincial Drug Administration, will "visit the province mask, body thermometer, antiviral drugs production and wholesale enterprises... to ensure that the epidemic prevention and control of drugs, medical equipment quality safety and market supply. "

In fact, with Wuhan separated by more than 100 kilometers of Xiantao is the country's famous disposable non-woven mask production base. Wang Ming, a mask contract factory manager in Xiantao, told the Financial Times that there was no need to hoard masks. He mentioned that whether civilian or medical masks, as long as there are filter materials, the process is the same, put into production quickly. Wang's factory produces as many as 30 million masks a month, mainly for export. At present, the factory stock of raw materials can be produced one hundred thousand medical-grade masks, civilian masks 7 million (anti-flying Foam) .

Wang Ming's factory had a holiday before the Spring Festival. Before the holiday, he and his colleagues around him had received orders for masks from Hong Kong and Macao. Some of them had orders of up to 2 million individual masks, the last urgent order from Wang's factory was received in early January. Since the outbreak, Wang and his colleagues have been waiting to see if work can start. They went to the Health Commission for consultation, if the product is received by a pharmaceutical company, they can get a pass, but Wang Ming is more worried about the raw material problem, their stock is only enough for a few days, the raw materials are not protective supplies, it is impossible to get a pass, we don't know how we're GONNA get in here.

Miao Xiaohui, an expert in public health clinical consultation in Shanghai, was involved in the prevention and control of SARS in Shanghai and Xiaotangshan in Beijing in 2003. Noted that Wuhan to build two temporary hospitals, Miao Xiaohui very confused. He said that after 2003, major cities across the country basically built new specialized hospitals to deal with public health emergencies, plus the original lung hospitals, so at least two hospitals can be dedicated to treating patients with new pneumonia, in particular, the government-funded Infectious Disease Hospital built after 2003 can and must assume similar functions as Xiaotangshan Hospital during SARS.

In his view, the expansion of new hospital space is important, but how to deploy existing resources, rapid response, in fact, more important. In fact, a gold and Silver Tan medical staff told this magazine, until January 25, gold and Silver Tan hospital still part of the ward idle, the main reason is not enough medical staff.

Avoid panic visits

▲▲▲

Avoid panic visits

So, on January 20, Zhong Nanshan gave an interview to CCTV, on January 22, Hubei Province launched a level II emergency response to a public health emergency, two days later it was upgraded to a level I response, and the provinces responded one after another within a week, people across China have experienced dramatic mood swings. Those in Wuhan at the center of the storm may feel it especially strongly.

Gao lanlan is Wuhan Qingshan people, she suspected that her father is too scared to fever. In late December, Gao Lanlan was one of the first to know about the outbreak and was on high alert through her friends in the medical community. She bought a mask early and alerted her friends in the community, but her father remained calm until Jan. 23, when the city of Wuhan was closed, when Gao Lanlan discussed the epidemic situation with her friends, the old man still told her not to spread rumors.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The elderly man's emotional turn came early on January 24, when the husband of a friend of Gotland's was quarantined and called to inform Gotland. On the first day, an old man died in the neighborhood of Gao Lanlan. Although it was later confirmed that it was caused by the flu, everyone was very suspicious. In addition, various kinds of collapse videos of medical staff went viral on wechat groups, and the old man's blood pressure soared rapidly, although he has recovered after taking the medicine, the old man has been in a panic.

The old man had a fever on January 25, and his temperature hovered between 37.3 and 37.4. GOLLAND's first reaction was to call the community and try to go through the grading process, but the community workers told Golland that they were not doctors and had no protection, also have no way, suggested to take the old man to Qingshan District, Wuhan appointed hospital nine hospital to see outpatient, or directly dial 120, and stressed that "dial 120 can definitely be admitted to the hospital. ".

Gao lanlan hesitates. She wants to quarantine her father at home, but the nearby pharmacies are closed. If she goes to the hospital, she knows that the 9 th hospital in Qingshan District, Wuhan is already full. Finally, or a civil servant friend told her, a few days ago to a large three-level hospital beds, in the vicinity of Gao Lan Lan Lan home, suggested that she try. After Gao Lan Lan took the old man past, just know here fever clinic has been open, in addition to the ambulance in and out, the whole hospital is very cold, Gao Lan father in front, only three patients.

In the hospital, Gao Lanlan's father checked a stream, b stream, also took a lung CT, finally the doctor judged, in addition to bronchitis, the old man is not sick, temporarily do not need to prescribe drugs. Early on the morning of January 26, the old man's temperature returned to normal, but no matter how Gao Lanlan Comfort, the old man always panic, always think they are in the incubation period. Like Gao Lanlan's father, many people may seek medical treatment in panic. Just when Gao Lanlan took his father to see a doctor, a middle-aged woman in front of them had already gone to the hospital three times in a week. The doctor repeatedly told her not to come again, and had another CT scan, make me sick even if I'm not sick.

That's why, in Miao's view, rescuing patients is one thing in the face of such a complex epidemic, but it's also important to lay a good foundation for the community. But to lay a good foundation for the community is not to hand over the decision to divert screening to the community. This is difficult to operate, and the people have no sense of trust. Instead, on the basis of complete protection, they go door to door, to help the government do a good job in epidemiological investigation, psychological comfort and science popularization, "what we need to do is some meticulous and professional work, and what we need to do is test the administrative wisdom of the local government, " Miao said.

According to our understanding, as of January 26, some community residents'committees and community hospitals had not received any notification, and training and protective materials were not available, which means that, as the most basic and important step in the current grading of diagnosis and treatment of new coronary pneumonia, community committees and hospitals, in addition to waiting for patients to come home, complete the information reported, the actual can do more limited work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
So far, Wuhan has virtually shut down all traffic, and Wu Hong estimates that with such measures, new infections will be immediately reduced, but the incubation period of the virus is up to two weeks, so at least two observation cycles will be needed, to consider whether to lift some of the measures.

As a young man with a high sensitivity to online information, Gotland panicked in early January, when most people around her didn't understand her. But on January 23rd, when a close friend called her at 3:00 in the morning and asked her if she wanted to buy a plane ticket to escape Wuhan Together, Gao lanlan looked at the little guy beside her and thought of the old man in the next room, think of their own in Wuhan more than 30 years of good life, and finally gave up the remaining tickets of the flight.

Today, in Wuhan, unlike a week ago, when the winds were calm and unpredictable, she sees daily surges of information about disease, the negative energy of shortages, and the positive energy of strangers and strangers looking out for each other. Each message offered a glimpse of the truth, and instead she calmed down and persuaded her father to believe in the power of the group.

(thanks to Wu Hong, Li Tong, Gao Lan, Wang Ming and Charles Lindbergh for their help and support in Wuhan. Interns Yang Yue and Zhang Jiajing contributed to this article.)

Progress: On the night of January 26, through community channels, Xu Cai's husband finally lined up a bed from the same level III hospital near his home in Gotland. On Jan. 28, Xu Cai's in laws were hospitalized after a long wait.

In the most difficult times, a friend picked up her husband from the hospital, a strange netizen at the door of her home, put down protective equipment, living materials, there are many neighbors to help her, everywhere to find medical channels. When her in laws could not be admitted to the hospital, she was advised to take them with her to the community board site, but she refused, no matter how hard it was, and did not want her family to become a source of infection.
